Taiwan Equity Movers: Clevo, Formosa International, Hannstar

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-05-26T05:43:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/china-steel-clevo-sinopac-shin-kong-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:14 a.m.  The Taiex Index rose 61.31, or 0.7 percent, to 8,788.40.  Clevo Co. (2362)  (2362 TT) gained 2.5 percent to NT$53.50, halting
an eight-day slump. The laptop maker plans to buy back 6 million
common shares, or 0.94 percent of its outstanding stock, at
between NT$50 and NT$62.5 each from today to June 25, the
Taipei-based company said in a statement to the stock exchange
yesterday.  Formosa International Hotels Corp. (2707)  (2707 TT) surged 5.8
percent to NT$562 after the  Central News Agency  reported
yesterday individual Chinese tourists will be allowed to visit
the island before the end of June, citing Lai Shin-yuan,
minister for Mainland Affairs Council.  Hannstar Display Corp. (6116)  (6116 TT) advanced 4.4 percent to
NT$5.03, the steepest increase since March 18, after the
Commercial Times reported the flat panel maker received orders
for Asustek Computer Inc.â€™s tablet computers, citing market
speculation. Justin Chien, an investor relations spokesman for
Hannstar, declined to comment on customer orders.  To contact the reporter on this story:
